Started reading the book this morning.
Got to page 40 before I left for work.
Saw the movie after work with Sarah.
The movie was AMAZING.

I thought the actors played Jacob, Edward, and Jasper (?) were cute.
xD;;

I'm continuing Twilight at the moment.
But ahhhhh.
I love it.
=)

Oh geez.
I've been entirely WAY too busy.
Haha.

School is getting kind of hectic.
I mean.
Besides dropping psych (because the teacher sucks and I'd rather have a W and retake it. Than an F and do the work for no reason.)
Second round of midterms are coming up.
October 22nd.
And.
Another essay for english.
(Not that I'm complaining. Haha. I love my english class.)
I'm kind of scared about chem.
But I've been studying hella. So hopefully I'll be fine. =)

Work has been ok.
I'm not closing on saturdays anymore!
Not next week, anyway.
I'm realllly glad about that.
Haha.
Whenever I work, I ALWAYS close.
>.<;;

23 hours for this week.
And 23 this upcominig one.
I'm hoping I get more hours.
Though.
They should be picking up sometime after Halloween, if not, then halfway through November.

In the past week, I've gone to the movies three times.
Went to see Nick and Norah's Infinite Playlist (my favorite part, of course, they talk briefly about The Beatles. ^_^)
And.
Quarantine.
Not that good of a movie.
But freaked me out a bit.

I have no idea what I'm doing on the 17th.
I know I'm doing something.
But I can't remember what.
>.<;;
I really need to learn to write down my hangouts so I don't make plans over them.

Whoaaaaaaaaaaa.

These past couple of weeks have been full of thinking. I've decided that I'm going to try and change my view of myself. I'm going to raise my self-esteem. I'll stick up for myself when I'm put down (or, at least, I'll try). I'm actually going to eat too. No more waiting until someone makes me eat. I'm losing more weight and it's disgusting. I don't want to go back down to 94.0 pounds. (Especially not since I have a doctor's appointment this Friday, but that's not the point.)

I'm sick of how I am. So I'm changing for the better, hopefully.

Ok. So I'm going to update this because I haven't in a while.

I went to the library on Friday and checked out 11 books. I have 5 books left to read. But I kind of don't want to read them anymore because I'm scared of the covers and then I get nightmares about witches trying to kill me, vampires, murders, and such.... o_O

So I was invited to go hang out with Kylie, Alan, and others for tomorrow, Tuesday, and Friday. But I can't because I'm <u>grounded</u>. =( For the whole summer. But I'm behaving more and, once I stop crying and "whining" and whatever, my dad might say I'm behaving too. Not like I'll count on that though.

<u>BUT</u> I can do Marching Band! =O

Hm... I need to start going to bed at reasonable hours. Not at 3 or 4 in the morning. And then waking up at 6 or 7. I'm so lame. U_U

So I'm in english class right now. Ugh. I don't want to be here. I'm too tired. I got like 6 hours of sleep though. =)

This morning, my dad started yelling at me about how I don't behave and how he doesn't want me in band my senior year. Whatever. It's not like I'll still not go to Marching Band practices or hang out in the band room.

Last night was my flute recital. I played Adante in C Major by Mozart. Oh my goodness. I sucked so much. It was horrible. I kept getting lost (I'm still having trouble trying to count and play at the same time). Then, I came in wrong once. And for my cadenza, I did a trill on the wrong note and I didn't even play all the right notes. My jaw was quivering and everything. It just really sucked.

I think I feel happier now? I don't know.
I feel numb and empty.
I thought I'd be crying. But I've already cried too much. I don't want to care anymore. As long as we're still friends, it's ok.

I hope this doesn't end up like last year.

There really seems no point in writing in this anymore. It seems like no one cares.

There's something going on between me and Matty. And I'm scared. I'm the one who started this problem. Now, I think he's going to break up with me tomorrow. I just wanted to tell him the truth. I wanted to tell him I weigh 98 lbs. Not because I was proud of how much I weigh but because I was scared and didn't know what to do. (Don't tell me to eat because it's really hard for me.)
I don't know if my stomach hurts because I'm hungry, I've eaten too much, I feel like I've lost a friend, or because I want to cry.

Happy Birthday Mami!

Yesterday was ok. Nathaniel's party was fun. Except I felt a bit sad. I felt like everyone had their friends and I was alone (so yeah. It was my own problem, Kilani. Nathaniel had nothing to do with it). But I felt a bit better when we got back to his house and kept watching movies.

Today is ok, I guess. It's mami's birthday and so I made her a cake. Diana (one of my sister's) is angry for some reason and won't help with anything. Whatever.

I hope you guys are having fun. =)

Today was fun. =) I saw Kristi, Sarah Burger, and Joe Burger at the mall. They went to go see Scary Movie 4. I was supposed to see that with Kristi. Maybe some other time though. =/

Birthday party tomorrow, Mami's birthday on Sunday, Katya's birthday on Monday, Devon's birthday on Thursday, Melo's birthday on the 26th (?), and Papi's and Tia Pati's on the 28th. Ugh. Too many birthdays.

Yeah...

It's pretty sad that I've just stopped caring.

I still have English homework that's due for tomorrow. I'll probably do it like at the beginning of class. Or something like that. Not like I can though. I have it second period and the homework is like looking up quotes in a book, I think.

I still have the whole back side of the Chem. worksheet. And I have no idea how to figure out the problems. I don't know how to figure out the change in heat. U_U And I doubt Mindy even had time to try to figure it out.

I didn't do like 2 math problems. I think I'm screwed in that class. Because of the score I got on my last test. I got a 44% on the last test and we have another test on Friday. I hope I get a good grade on the test. I have a 70.4% in that class right now.

The good thing is... I did my spanish homework while waiting for Jackie's flute lesson to end today. =)



The bad thing was... the AP review was horrendous. When I was trying to pay attention, others were talking. It bothers me when I can't hear because others are talking. It doesn't help me, either, that I'm a horrible notes taker. =/


The highlight of the night may have been when Andrew sent me a song. It's very pretty. It's Bach's 1st unaccompanied Cello Suite. Either that or when I went to flute lessons and my tone wasn't as disgusting as it usually is. ^_^  I'm getting better. Yay.



My mom said that it sounds like I have turberculosis. But the doctor said it sounds like bronchitis? Eh. I don't know. Nor do I really care.

Yesterday was a bit fun. Brooke gave me a ride to Hayes Mansion. Hung out in the girl's room until it was time for us to find our seats. My seat was next to Nathaniel and Alison. I wish I sat next to Mari and Minji though. It looked like they had a great time. When Ladies Jazz went to perform, Jovany, Nathaniel, and I were the only ones left at our table. Jazz 2 went to warm up. We performed. I didn't play for most of the songs. I got lost in Blues in the Closet and St. Thomas; I played as much as I had memorized. I couldn't really see my music from the stand because I left my glasses at home. Swing Kids were great. Minji, Brooke, Linda, and I danced during their first few songs. Jazz 1 was awesome. I danced with Brooke during their last song. It was pretty fun. I got a ride home from Sarah Zoobi. Got home at around 12:40-ish. It was great. =)

Sadly, I didn't have a great time. I probably would've had a better time if Lucy were there. Or if I had gone to Spanish Camp instead. I wanted to go but I couldn't because of A Night of Jazz. U_U
There really isn't any point to writing in this thing anymore, is there?

I'm so bored.

This weekend was boring. But that's what I get for going to movie nights on Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday night. Lol.

I can't wait for tomorrow!

=D

Sorry I didn't call you today. I was totally going to call. I even wrote it down. But I forgot. Forgive me?



Anyway...
I went to Kristi's house. We went to Suzanne's house. Then to the park. Afterwards, Kristi and I went back to her house and waited for Nathan (a friend of Joe's) and Joe to come over. Also, Pam and Matt came over. All of us went into the Jacuzzi and played Truth or Dare. Then after Joe and Nathan left to go eat dinner, Matt, Pam, Kristi and I went to McDonald's (like at 8:30) and went to some video place and rented Poltergeist. It wasn't that scary. Joe and Nathan came over like at 9 and we watched the movie. Afterwards, we all played Twister and then I left. Like at 11:30.

Today (yesterday, actually) was kind of fun.
=)

I hate when this happens.
I don't see the point in anything anymore.
The sad thing is, I did this to myself.

=(

This morning (or yesterday?) an old "friend" found me on Myspace. I didn't think he remembered who I was because it's me and well, everyone'll forget about me.

The last thing I remember about him is in sixth grade when he said I wasn't cool because I didn't let him cut in line. The sad thing is, I used to like him before he said that to me.

I wish I am the way I used to be, when I could quickly get over a guy. It's not so easy now...



I miss Mathson. I miss Drama Club. I'd even go back to the day when I got suspended, if it means just one more day in sixth grade. I'd go back to when Vianey and I were bullied. I'd even go back to when I had "0" period (at seven a.m.) to go to PE since I was in band. =(

I miss Arbuckle too though. I miss Mr. Conder and watching Michael Jackson music videos in his class. I miss that first day of school when I thought Vianey was held back just because she was taller than everyone.

I was really stupid back then. But hey, it's better to be stupid and all than to know more and feel as if nothing can ever really make you happy.

=/

You know... most of all, I think I miss having braces. =)

Today was super fun.

The only problem was that my back was bothering me as it has for more than a month.

Can someone please put me out of my misery? I can't stand, sit, or lie down without my back hurting.

I was listening to "Cruella De Vil" earlier. It made me so sad. Not because the character is horrible, but because I saw it once. With... well, with someone.

=/


I can't wait until tomorrow. I won't be home for most of the day! =) 
I'm so excited.


I really need sleep. This week I got (in order): four hours of sleep (Monday), four and a half hours of sleep (Tuesday), five hours of sleep (Wednesday), and five and a half hours of sleep (last night).

I'm really sleepy. I've been getting between 4 and 5 hours of sleep each night. Argh. So tired... and I still have to finish my math homework and work on my English project. Maybe later...
